column2: Port Entry Officer
The search?
You're right.{nl}We are currently searching the area because some people on the list of refugees are missing from the ship that came from Moroth Embassy.

But the thing is, we looked from the top to the bottom of the ship but can't find any trace of the missing people.{nl}We were starting to think that they probably didn't get on board in the first place.
It will be a great help if you, Revelator, would help us.
By the way, there was something I wanted to ask someone strong and who can travel, like you.
We found something that was in the possession of a demon while searching the ship coming from Moroth Embassy.
From our investigation, the name {#003399}
{/} was spotted.{nl}It's a common name, but something seems fishy about it, especially because we found it from a demon's possession.
Please investigate if there's a traitor among the humans,{nl}and if it has anything to do with the disappearance.
We've already done our bit of investigating ourselves.
There's someone called Nijole at the Fasika Plateau, Gateway of the Great King, and Igti Coast. Please start there.
What?{nl}Introduce myself?{nl}
I...my name is Nijole, and I'm from Nestospa.{nl}I bear the faith to trust the Goddess until the very...{nl}
Wait.{nl}Who are you anyway?
I see. What a case.{nl}I understand now, but I have nothing to do with what happened there.{nl}It's been a great while since I left this place.
You can ask around if you can't believe me.
My name?{nl}I'm Nijole.{nl}I'm with the researchers here.
I don't always stay here, but spent most of my life around here.{nl}As you'd very well know, there's a lot going on in this place that intrigues a researcher's curiosity ever since the Medzio Diena.
I'm sorry for those who went missing.{nl}I hope they're all safe.
I am Nijole.{nl}A Loremaster, following the Goddess Jurate.
People are missing from the ship that entered Orsha?{nl}And a name same as mine came out from the demon's possession, I see.
So you mean there were two ships that left Moroth Embassy,{nl}and some refugees boarded the wrong one and got attacked by the demon.
So, who was that person called 'Nijole'?
Excuse me?{nl}You mean it's just a herb?
Well, that was meaningless..
I'll report that we requested you, Revelator, to rescue the missing people.
Did everything go fine?{nl}
A...herb?{nl}And did they buy that excuse?{nl}
{nl}It doesn't matter.{nl}That's not the important part.{nl}{nl}Are you ready?
Please complete the request with Demon God Nijole's presence hidden from the person who asked you to investigate.{nl}After that we will enter the area of Goddess Jurate.
Didn't you leave?{nl}If you have any doubt left, please understand that this is a misunderstanding.
I get it that your mission is important,{nl}but I hope you don't take up too much of my time.{nl}I am really, really busy at the moment.
Revelator of Moroth (15)
It's nothing.

I will help the search
Not my business

I feel a little relieved to see that I have arrived safely.
After having clues and tracking the whereabouts of the Beholder, I found out that he was hiding somewhere here.
It is too dangerous to put soldiers in large scale{nl}because this place is like a secret place created by Lord Delmore.
That's why I asked only Pajauta, you, and a few soldiers to come.
I'm sure the Beholder is here.{nl}Let's search where he is hidden.
When you're ready to crush his ambitions, let's move on.
Something's not right.
What is Beholder trying to do here?
It's not good. If there is no conclusion here...
Soldiers are agitated.{nl}I'll leave after I calm down the soldiers.{nl}Please investigate the sign that just occurred with Pajauta.
I guess there were rumors among soldiers.
It is one of the general's duty to calm down the agitated soldiers.
So, let's do our job well too!{nl}While I look around the area, stay here and clear the monsters around there.
There is not much time.{nl}Let's do our own works quickly.
Seems like General Ramin is done reorganizing the soldiers.{nl}Let's go!
First, I've taken a step to the agitated soldiers.
Let's start the investigation.{nl}Are you ready?
However, there is not enough information to move with the agitated soldiers.{nl}First, I'll go back to Orsha to organize the soldiers,{nl}and get information from Lord Inesa.
Until then, please gather all the information you can with Pajauta.
Until General Ramin is back from Orsha, we'd better do what we can.
I looked around while you were hunting the monsters{nl}and there were red traces here and there.

This feels like Kruvina from way long ago. I've felt a magic wave similar to the vibration just now from those. Could you please find out if there is any kind of crystal that emits red traces like this in the Liepsnos Waiting Area?{nl}I will look into the red traces that I've been investigating.
Judging by these traces, it looks like a Kruvina...
I guess I was right, seeing you coming from that direction.{nl}Hand me those red crystals.
Just like what I expected, the red crystal you've brought is related to {#003399}Kruvina{/}.
If your prediction is right, the monsters around the center of the waiting area will also have these red crystals stuck into them.{nl} If you follow that path, you may meet the Beholder.
Let's meet after defeating monsters along the way to collect the crystals from them.{nl}This red crystal will be useful.
You came right away.{nl}Now, the crystals you brought will help open this barrier.
Let's get close to the barrier.
If the red crystal is really pure Kruvina,{nl}and the barrier is the Beholder's barrier, we might be able to break the barrier...!
Go ahead.
Nice work.{nl}Did you find out anything?
That's a scroll.{nl}Of course. Answer is always near the question.
Now, let's remove that barrier with this scroll.{nl}That will be your job.{nl}I'll stand guard.
Please remove the barrier.{nl}Your Divine Energy will be enough to make the scroll react.
Barrier is removed.{nl}March toward the Hidden Passage.
The Beholder must have activated the barrier after entering here through the Waiting Area.{nl}Let's go inside.
Bad vibe here...{nl}You must find and destroy the Beholder here...
According to the information from Orsha,{nl}Delmore Rephaim has set up magic control devices in various places{nl}just in case he loses control of Kruvina's power.
Regardless of whether the Beholder used them or not,{nl} it would be good to find the control device and find a way to control their magic.{nl}To prepare for later and secure a way to the depths.
Here's the map that has the location of control device...
Monster attacking just as I opened the map with the location of the control device...{nl}Is this a coincidence?
Anyway, since we've stopped the attack, let me tell you about the magic control device.
We now must control 4 magic control devices.
The first magic control device is at the Delmore Entryway. Go and check.
For the other side, you go, Pajauta.
Go to the first device marked on this page and activate it.{nl} The location is marked on the map.
The control device didn't work?{nl}Perhaps it exhausted its magic power while it's been out of use for a long time.
In preparation for such a situation, the lord of Orsha gave her pendant.{nl}It is said that although it is a small pendant, it can have a large amount of magic power.
If you defeat the nearby monsters and inject the magic power into the pendant, you will be able to operate the control device again.
Defeat the nearby enemies and fill the magic power to the pendant.
Great.{nl}This will do.
There seems to have enough magic power in the pendant.{nl}Bring it to the control device and activate it.
Did the Magic Control Device activate?
The first Magic Control Device is activated.
Of course. It seems that the unpleasant feeling of intense pressure has disappeared a bit after the control device is activated.{nl}You did a great job.
It is time to activate the rest of the Magic Control Device.{nl}Well... It looks like it's just past Central Square.
Join Pajauta at the Central Square and go together.
You okay?
The Beholder's last must be...
Oh, I have to talk to general Ramin.{nl}Can we have a minute alone?
To be ambushed while being careless for a while... {nl}What a shame.
Anyway, let's quickly activate the control device and chase the Beholder.
I'll come back after checking the soldiers.{nl}If something happens, talk to Pajauta.
I almost felt the second Magic Control Device working right away!{nl}Great job!
The last Magic Control Device should be fine. The pendant's magic power is still enough.{nl}Let's activate the last Magic Control Device right away.
Things are progressing well.{nl}Now let's...
What was the vibration and loud noise?{nl}General Ramin, have you heard it?
What was that loud noise?
The loud noise was from activating the last Magic Control Device?{nl}Let's head to Central Square, the source of the sound.
Finally arrived at the Assembly Hall where the Beholder is hiding.{nl}We can specify the location of Beholder.{nl}I guess he's up to something here.
There is a barrier where Beholder is likely to be.{nl}I haven't heard from the lord from here.
Revelator, your power may destroy the barrier.{nl}Destroy the barrier.
We are running out of time.{nl}Hurry up and destroy the barrier.
It even can't be destroyed by the divine energy of the one who received the revelation...?{nl}Pajauta, there must be another way.

I felt it from the waiting area {nl}There is also a Kruvina here that I thought had disappeared a long time ago, and that Kruvina didn't respond much to the barrier.{nl}It seemed something more powerful... is guarding this magic barrier.
I did some research hoping my expectation was wrong, but...
This is...
I thought it's all destroyed...
I guess there are several {#003399}Mirtinas{/} like this, and that power is keeping the barrier up.
We must find the {#003399}Mirtinas{/} and destroy it.
The {#003399}Mirtinas{/} must be destroyed once found.
....{nl}Pajauta...
The destruction of the world...{nl}The Beholder was planning such a terrible thing...{nl}We must do something.
Let's stop the Beholder's plan, and save Pajauta.
I must tell the princess how serious the situation is.{nl}I want you to go to Orsha and tell the lord about this.
Revelator, your back.{nl}Where is Pajauta and General Ramin?
Beholder took Pajauta and disappeared, and the Beholder's real goal is to destroy the Divine Tree...
I can't believe this...{nl}Although... I don't think you're lying.

Just in case, General Ramin and the Revelator have dispatched an investigation team to the area where they have gone before.{nl}We will inform you immediately when we find any traces related to the Revelator.
It seems that the investigative team at the Magic Association Assembly Hall has found something.{nl}Please head to the Magic Association Assembly Hall.
Inesa Hamondale
Seems to have a trace in Magic Association Assembly Hall.{nl}Let's check in case it may be information about the Beholder.

Hello Revelator, I am investigating here under the command of the lord.
Some of our investigators have gone inside that crystal to investigate and have not returned.
One day, a note fell out from the crystal.{nl}The note said that the Reservoir of Corruption is alive.
There's a story that what we're planning to kill are the clones.{nl}According to the note, the investigators are being chased by the Spreader.{nl}Please save my colleagues.
Revelator... Thanks for helping us...
I'll go back to the Turbulent Core and find the bodies and belongings of my dead colleagues.
Thank you for keeping out from more damage.
Magic Control Device that Pajauta has activated.{nl}Pajauta seems to have controlled the magic power of the Magic Control Device.

We've found where the Beholder is while investigating inside the battlefield.{nl}General Ramin and Pajauta are already headed to where Beholder is.
Please borrow your power too, Revelator.
Please go to the Delmore Waiting Area by passing the Delmore Garden.{nl}If there is something I can help with, I'll be delighted to help.
I'm busy at the moment.

Revelator, we've been searching for Pajauta ever since her disappearance, but we're coming up empty handed.
Along with the search we are praying to the Goddess, but she does not answer them.
Maybe you might be able to get some answers?
May the Blessing of the Goddess be with you.
I've been expecting you. Revelator.
We had you come here through Neringa, so we might help you on your journey to solve the two problems that you face.
Two questions being the whereabouts of {#003399}Pajauta{/} and the Beholder.
Of the two, the one who can put the world in peril is the Beholder. I will start with his whereabouts.
Beholder was once a Demon God... he has gone to Novaha to find his true form.
All his evil deeds carried out for so long... it was all to awaken the sealed gloves of the Demon God with the powers of Kruvina and chaos...
You will be guided from the Goddess Statue here to Novaha.
Revelator?{nl}What brings you here...
Ah, after the incident I figured my sister and I couldn't live with the villagers, so we are just hiding out here in the Bracken Forest.
It has been so long we thought you'd forgotten about us.{nl}What's going on?
At the time...
You, Revelator, saved us from befalling a victim to the Wizard at the Bracken Forest.
However we were test subjects for an experiment, and we thought the bracken spores we carry might infect the villagers, the reason why we can't go back...
After that I somewhat recovered....
My sister Rose isn't showing any signs of recovery.{nl}I don't know what to do.
All I can do is keep Rose alive with what little herbs I can find around here.
Beholder?
The mysterious Wizard who used us for his experiment, is that his name?{nl}I didn't see him.
Rose might know something but in her condition I doubt she could finish a sentence.

Secret Melody

they must have returned
